   {:e #blake3 "aeac43651d4abc5f37c5179ccc955b80a9ed57ad5fa159ba923cb7e1765177dc" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: After 3 external sessions, analyze the data and draw conclusions. This is the empirical verdict on the UAQ hypothesis. APPROACH: (1) Collect all calibration data from external store. (2) Compute: mean_error trend across sessions, per-type error breakdown, composition quality (product vs what we'd get with weighted-sum on same data). (3) Compare to braid self-development baseline: 36 sessions to reach mean_error 0.224. External should reach < 0.15 in 3 sessions if UAQ hypothesis is correct. (4) Identify: what worked (which recommendation types had lowest error?), what failed (which had highest?), what surprised us (unexpected patterns?). (5) Crystallize findings as ADR-FOUNDATION-026 (UAQ Empirical Validation). Include: yes/no verdict, evidence, adjustments needed. (6) If verdict is NO: document why, identify which of the four factors failed, propose architectural revision. (7) If verdict is YES: plan Phase E (daemon, active observer) with confidence that the core architecture is validated. ACCEPTANCE: (A) ADR-FOUNDATION-026 crystallized with empirical data. (B) Clear yes/no verdict on UAQ hypothesis. (C) If yes: next phase planned. If no: revision path documented. DEPENDS-ON: DOGFOOD-2." :op :assert}
